What is Exception Propagation?

When an exception occurs inside a method and is not handled there, JVM transfers the exception object to the calling method.

This process continues until:

An appropriate catch block is found
OR main() is reached
OR JVM terminates the program

This movement of exception from one method to another is called Exception Propagation.

Real-Life Example

Imagine a company hierarchy:

Employee
   |
Team Lead
   |
Manager
   |
Director

Suppose Employee cannot solve an issue.

The issue goes to Team Lead.

If Team Lead cannot solve it, it goes to Manager.

If Manager cannot solve it, it goes to Director.

Same thing happens with exceptions.

Method3()
   |
Method2()
   |
Method1()
   |
main()
Exception moves upward until someone handles it.
public class PropagationDemo {

    static void method3() {
        int result = 10 / 0;
    }

    static void method2() {
        method3();
    }

    static void method1() {
        method2();
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        method1();
    }
}

