Call Stack and Exception Propagation

JVM maintains a stack called Call Stack.

Top
-------
m3()
m2()
m1()
main()
-------
Bottom

When exception occurs:

m3() removed
m2() removed
m1() removed
main() removed

This process is called Stack Unwinding.

